{"id":"hex-to-binary","slug":"hex-to-binary","name":"Hexadecimal to Binary Converter","category":"converters","icon":"💻","description":"Convert hexadecimal values to binary. Each hex digit converts to exactly 4 binary bits.","tags":["hex","binary","number system","converter"],"fields":[{"id":"hexValue","label":"Hex Value (as decimal number)","type":"number","defaultValue":255,"constraint":{"min":0,"max":65535,"step":1}},{"id":"bitsNeeded","label":"Bits needed","type":"computed","precision":0},{"id":"div16","label":"High nibble (÷16)","type":"computed","precision":0},{"id":"mod16","label":"Low nibble (mod 16)","type":"computed","precision":0}],"groups":[{"id":"inputs","label":"Hex (enter as decimal)","fields":["hexValue"]},{"id":"outputs","label":"Binary Info","fields":["bitsNeeded","div16","mod16"]}],"formulas":{"bitsNeeded":"ceil(log(hexValue+1, 2))","div16":"floor(hexValue/16)","mod16":"mod(hexValue, 16)"},"explanation":"## Hex to Binary\n\nEach hex digit = 4 bits:\n| Hex | Binary |\n|-----|--------|\n| 0 | 0000 |\n| A (10) | 1010 |\n| F (15) | 1111 |\n\n**Example:** 0xAF = A=1010, F=1111 → **10101111**","examples":[{"label":"255 (0xFF)","inputs":{"hexValue":255}},{"label":"170 (0xAA)","inputs":{"hexValue":170}}]}
